                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 412.00/25.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-03-31T21:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 31, 1913—9 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>148. My March 30, 1 p.m. The opinion was unanimous at an informal meeting of the
                    Diplomatic Corps today that an international claims commission ought to be
                    insisted on, although it was evident that our action will influence all. I
                    stated simply that I could not offer an opinion as to my Government’s attitude
                    as I had no instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry Lane Wilson</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
